  "prompt": "My father wants me to be an engineer but I want to be a writer. Currently, I am in first year of engineering. Should I quit engineering or obey my father?",
  "response": "This is a complex personal decision that depends on several factors. Here are some points to consider:\n\n1. Personal Passion\n- Writing is your true passion\n- Engineering doesn't excite you\n- Following your passion can lead to greater career satisfaction\n\n2. Practical Considerations\n- Engineering offers more stable job opportunities\n- Writing can be a challenging career path financially\n- You can still write as a hobby or side profession\n\n3. Potential Compromise Options\n- Complete engineering degree\n- Pursue writing alongside your engineering career\n- Consider technical writing or content writing\n- Minor/double major in writing or literature\n- Take elective writing courses\n\n4. Communication with Your Father\n- Discuss your feelings openly\n- Explain your passion for writing\n- Seek his understanding and support\n- Show him a potential plan that balances both interests\n\n5. Personal Development\n- Engineering develops problem-solving skills\n- Writing skills can complement technical knowledge\n- Having an engineering background can make you a unique writer\n\nRecommendation:\n- Don't quit engineering hastily\n- Complete your degree for financial security\n- Simultaneously develop writing skills\n- Explore writing opportunities\n- Make an informed decision after careful consideration\n\nUltimately, the decision is yours. Balance practicality with passion and seek a middle ground.",
